      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLARELY TOM (2) was far from disgraced after being in contention on the turn to finish half a length away in second last start over 1207m at this track. That followed a win on debut at this track. Finds a suitable race and can figure in the finish. SOUPER VINNIE (1) has switched yards since finishing third four weeks ago over 1207m at this track. One of the genuine hopes in the race. BENNY'S CANDY MAN (3) recorded a strong maiden win over 1106m at this track (Dirt) last time, getting there by 6 lengths. Sparingly raced and has more to offer. Winning rider A R Rodriguez stays aboard and he should be in the finish again. THICK AS THIEVES (5) returns after a spell of seven months. Started the last campaign impressively when in the placings over 1609m at Fairgrounds Turf. Yet to win first up but generally runs well with two minor placings from four tries. Can make his presence felt.",
